The ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has pegged its expression of interest and nomination forms for Ekiti and Osun states governorship elections at N22.5 million. The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has fixed June 18, 2022 for Ekiti governorship election and July 16, 2022 for that of Osun state. According to details of the timetable released by the party on Tuesday, the expression of interest form would go for N2.5 million while nomination form would be sold for N20 million. This was contained in the timetable and schedule of activities for the elections released by the National Secretary of APC Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC), John Akpanudode. Also Read:Â Anambra APC Sacks Publicity Secretary For Congratulating Soludo However, the party pegged the price for female aspirants and physically challenged aspirants to 50% of the prescribed fees. It said the sale of forms for the Ekiti state poll would commence on 16th November, 2021, while last day for submission of completed forms and accompanying documents to the national secretariat would be on 11th January, 2022. According to the statement, the sale of forms for the Osun election would commence on 18th November, 2021, while last day for submission of completed forms and accompanying documents would be 18th February, 2022.